-- Dollar Weakens Versus Most Counterparts as Greek Debt-Accord Concern Eases
-- B y   M a s a k i   K o n d o
-- 2012-01-31T02:45:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-31/dollar-weakens-versus-most-counterparts-as-greek-debt-accord-concern-eases.html
The dollar weakened against all but
one of its 16 major peers as speculation  Greece  will reach a
debt-swap agreement with bondholders reduced demand for the
currency as a refuge.  The greenback fell 0.3 percent to $1.3182 per euro as of
11:43 a.m. in  Tokyo .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Masaki Kondo in Singapore at 
